claims:
1. A computer-implemented method comprising:
receiving, at a server system including a computer processor, a request for a web page from a member of a social network service;
in response to receiving the request for the web page from the member, accessing a plurality of content items available for presentation within the requested web page, each content item being designated as having a content item type selected from one of a plurality of content item types in the group: an advertisement, an offer, a coupon, an activity feed item, a network update item, a blog post, and an article;
identifying a context in which the content items are to be presented to the member;
based on the context, selecting one or more content item types from the plurality of content item types, the one or more content item types associated with content items from which a highest ranking content item is to be selected for including in the web page requested by the member;
determining for content items having a content item type in the selected one or more content item types a specific user action that may be performed based at least in part on the identified context and the selected one or more content item types, wherein the specific user action is one of: a click response, a non-click response, a hover response, and a conversion response;
for each particular content item in the plurality of content items having a content item type corresponding with the selected one or more content item types, a likelihood score that represents a calculated likelihood that the first member will perform the specific user action if the particular content item is presented to the member, the likelihood score calculated in part by:
accessing member provided information in a member profile of the member of the social network service
using the member profile information, generating a prediction model for the member; and
using the prediction model to generate a likelihood score for each of the particular content items having a content item type corresponding with the selected one or more content item types;
ranking the content items based on the generated likelihood scores;
selecting the highest ranked content item for inclusion in the webpage requested by the member; and
transmitting the requested webpage for presentation to the member, the requested webpage including presentation of the selected highest ranked content item.
2. The method of claim 1, wherein the generated likelihood score is based, at least in part, on the identified context of the requested web page.
